-0.03}$ Gyr. Both constraints are consistent, and the derived\nSFRD agrees with previous studies and simulations. Additionally, we estimate\nthe galaxy bias $b$ of KiDS galaxies from the constrained HOD parameters and\nyield an increasing bias from $b=1.1_{-0.31}^{+0.17}$ at $z=0$ to\n$b=1.96_{-0.64}^{+0.18}$ at $z=1.5$. Finally, we provide a forecast for future\ngalaxy surveys and conclude that, due to their considerable depth, future\nsurveys will yield a much tighter constraint on the evolution of the SFRD.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Apr 2022 16:55:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 11 Sep 2022 15:43:56 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 18 Nov 2022 10:06:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-21"}
