h becomes\nnegative at Hubbard $U \\sim 11$ eV, indicating incipient pairing tendencies.\nFinally, we also looked at various cases of hole doping that always exhibit\ntight pairs. Thus, we believe our results for Na$_2$Cu$_2$TeO$_6$ could provide\nguidance to experimentalists and theorists working on this dimerized chain\nsystem, such as short-range magnetic coupling, doping effects, and possible\npairing tendencies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Apr 2022 17:56:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-16"}
