eases with the rise in the $B$\nfield and can go over $100\\%$, when both $B$ and $q/m$ are large enough (say\n$B\\approx1$ and $q/m>2.2$)}. It is worth noting that the existence of regions\naway from the horizon where $g_{tt}>0$ also favors the energy-extraction\nprocess away from the effect of the black hole. However, the energy extraction\nfrom these regions is pure consequence of the magnetic field.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Apr 2022 07:05:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 25 Jul 2022 10:05:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-26"}
